# Prisma & Database Conventions

## Schema location
`apps/api/prisma/schema.prisma` — single source of truth for all models.

## Key models (quick reference)
| Model | Unique constraint | Notes |
|-------|------------------|-------|
| `Business` | `slug` | Tenant root |
| `User` | `username` | Roles: SUPER_ADMIN, BUSINESS_ADMIN, STAFF |
| `Appointment` | — | Links customer + service + staff + business |
| `Conversation` | `[businessId, phone]` | WhatsApp thread |
| `Lead` | — | Pipeline: NEW → CONTACTED → QUALIFIED → CONVERTED |
| `SupportTicket` | — | Statuses: OPEN, IN_PROGRESS, RESOLVED |
| `Payment` | `appointmentId` | One payment per appointment |
| `Service` | — | `priceCents` integer; `durationMin` integer |
| `BusinessFeature` | `[businessId, key]` | Feature flags |

## Migration workflow
```bash
# Create a new migration (dev)
cd apps/api
npx prisma migrate dev --name describe_your_change

# Deploy existing migrations (CI / prod)
npx prisma migrate deploy

# After schema changes, regenerate client
npx prisma generate
```

## Multi-tenancy rule (critical)
```typescript
// ✅ Every query scoped to businessId
await prisma.service.findMany({ where: { businessId } });

// ✅ Upsert using stable unique keys
await prisma.businessHours.upsert({
  where: { businessId_weekday: { businessId, weekday } },
  create: { ... },
  update: { ... },
});

// ❌ Never query without businessId unless intentional (e.g. seed, superadmin)
await prisma.appointment.findMany(); // WRONG in a tenant context
```

## Money
Store as **integer cents** — `priceCents`, `amountCents`. Never floats.

## Seed
`apps/api/prisma/seed.ts` — always upsert, never raw insert, so re-runs are safe.
Run: `npm run db:seed` (from `apps/api/`).

## Avoid N+1
Use `include` / `select` at query time. Never lazy-load inside loops.
```typescript
// ✅ Single query with includes
const appts = await prisma.appointment.findMany({
  where: { businessId },
  include: { service: true, customer: true },
});

// ❌ N+1
for (const appt of appts) {
  const svc = await prisma.service.findUnique({ where: { id: appt.serviceId } });
}
```
